  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Argentina</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project offers for those underprivileged children and young with problems with authorities, an opportunity to get legal assistance for free in cases when their human rights are violated. In special &#xE2;&#x80;&#x9C;juridical clinics&#xE2;&#x80;&#x9D; under aged people can also get general information about their rights, besides the mentioned free legal assistance. Projects objective: to change the prevailing situation in which the rights of under aged are many times left unrecognized at the institutional level in practice. Moreover, at the clinics, law students and recently graduated also get a chance to gain abilities for the future to handle cases related children&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99;s rights. Through them the project aims to incorporate a new paradigm into the institutional level taking these rights in account at the court instance.</narrative>
  </description>
